    "When interacting with an AI labelled as human (human-AI-perceived-as-human interaction; grey line) or humans labelled as AI (human-AI-perceived-as-human interaction; pink line), participants' bias increased but less than for the human-AI interaction (n = 200 participants).",
    "The shaded areas and error bars represent s.e.m.",
    "Article https://doi.org/10.1038/s41562-024-02077-2 Human-AI Human-AI perceived as human Human-human perceived as AI Human-human",
    "2 3 4 5 6 Article https://doi.org/10.1038/s41562-024-02077-2 AI trained on biased human data amplifies the bias.",
    "Next, we used a CNN 7 to classify each array of faces into more happy or more sad."
